parameters.name: BX
parameters.description: Magnetic field X component GSE or GSM coordinate

parameters.name: BY_GSE
parameters.description: Magnetic field Y component GSE coordinates

parameters.name: BZ_GSE
parameters.description: Magnetic field Z component GSE coordinates

parameters.name: BY_GSM
parameters.description: Magnetic field Y component GSM coordinates

parameters.name: BZ_GSM
parameters.description: Magnetic field Z component GSM coordinates

parameters.name: STD_DEV_BX
parameters.description:
Standard deviation of the BX component       
      in the averaging window.

parameters.name: STD_DEV_BY_GSE
parameters.description:
Standard deviation of the BY GSE             
      component in the averaging window.

parameters.name: STD_DEV_BZ_GSE
parameters.description:
Standard deviation of the BZ GSE             
      component in the averaging window.

parameters.name: STD_DEV_BY_GSM
parameters.description:
Standard deviation of the BY GSM             
      component in the averaging window.

parameters.name: STD_DEV_BZ_GSM
parameters.description:
Standard deviation of the BZ GSM             
      component in the averaging window.

parameters.name: STD_DEV_BMAG
parameters.description:
Standard deviation of the B-field            
      magnitude in the averaging window.

parameters.name: NPTS
parameters.description: Number of data points in the average.

parameters.name: DQF
parameters.description:
Data quality flag. 0 indicates good          
      data with no warnings. Each bit in the integer value print              
      indicates a particular type of data corruption. Correctable errors      
      have DQF values less than 32768. Larger values should be avoided.       
      This DQF column gives the largest value in the average.

parameters.name: X
parameters.description:
Distance from the Earth along the            
      Earth-Sun line, positive towards the Sun, in units of Re.

parameters.name: Y_GSE
parameters.description:
Distance from the Earth along the            
      dawn-dusk meridian, positive towards dusk, in units of Re.

parameters.name: Z_GSE
parameters.description:
Distance from the Earth above or below       
      the ecliptic plane (positive 'northwards') in units of Re.

parameters.name: Y_GSM
parameters.description:
Distance from the Earth along the GSM        
      Y-direction in units of Re.

parameters.name: Z_GSM
parameters.description:
Distance from the Earth along the GSM        
      Z-direction in units of Re.
